Step 1:
  Update Packages: sudo yum update (for Amazon Linux) or sudo apt update (for Ubuntu)

Step 2:
  Install Java: sudo yum install java-17-amazon-corretto -y (for Amazon Linux) or sudo apt install java-17-amazon-corretto -y(for Ubuntu)

Step 3:
  Add the Jenkins repo using the following command:
    wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo

Step 4:
  Import a key file from Jenkins-CI to enable installation from the package:
    rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key

Step 5:
  Install Jenkins using below command:
    yum install jenkins -y

Step 6:
  Enable Jenkins:
    systemctl enable jenkins

Step 7:
  Start Jenkins:
    systemctl start jenkins

Your Jenkins Server is Now up and running...........
